      "id": "ef1849c9_25afb543",
      "file_path": "services/hv-ves-client/producer/api/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/services/hvves/client/producer/api/HvVesProducer.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "Ok, but if this is only for inserting some bad data and we are expecting to use it ONLY in tests conditions we should mark this fact in this description. e.g. Something like \"Method for test purposes. Do not use it on production\"\nBut even though term \"message\" is too enigmatic.\nWhat messages? VesEvents as a raw?\nWTP message as a raw? ...\nOrdinary developer-\"user\" of our lib could feel lost.\nMaybe instead of \"ves event as a raw\", mark it with \"payload of WTP as a raw\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2837,
        "name": "Kornel Janiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kornel.janiak@nokia.com",
        "username": "kjaniak"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-07 06:40:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "056cc6f3_eb50bd3b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9ee68be7_f3b999df",
      "file_path": "services/hv-ves-client/producer/api/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/services/hvves/client/producer/api/HvVesProducer.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "Actually it's not for test purposes. It's more generic version of the other send method. Right now we're sending only ves events, but in the future someone could want to send some other message types. That's why we have payloadId field in wire frame. I think, that target user should not know about such thing like wire frame, only about the payload they want to send (VesEvent or some other message type), then the \"message\" term isn't ambiguous. Someone other should make they statement about this though.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3081,
        "name": "Jakub Dudycz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jakub.dudycz@nokia.com",
        "username": "dudini1"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-07 09:59:51.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ef1849c9_25afb543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "99c2e304_d72227fd",
      "file_path": "services/hv-ves-client/producer/api/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/services/hvves/client/producer/api/HvVesProducer.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "You both are right :) The use case is exactly like Jakub has described it and Kornel is right that a user might be a little lost. Lets change the method names to send(p<v>) and sendRaw(p<bb>, t). Also please enhance the JavaDoc with the insight from your last message, Jakub.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2683,
        "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
        "username": "jaszczur"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-07 10:16:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9ee68be7_f3b999df",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
